The paper deals with communication complexity and streaming, which are both fundamental topics in theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves information theory and data mining, which are covered by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DM (Data Mining), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the Approximate Matching problem, which is a classic problem in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
